The paper deals with algorithmic and combinatorial aspects of the Lovasz Local Lemma, which is a fundamental tool in discrete mathematics. The paper discusses the Moser-Tardos algorithm, which is a powerful algorithmic approach to the LLL, and its variants. The paper also discusses the MT-distribution concept and its applications in algorithmic and enumerative settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
